23/10/2009
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The trial of former Bosnian Serb commander Zdravko Tolimir will begin on December 17th at The Hague war crimes tribunal, the court announced on Thursday (October 22nd).
Tolimir is accused of genocide and other crimes stemming from the 1995 Srebrenica massacre of Muslims.
Preparations for the start of the trial have been delayed due to Tolimir's poor health.
(B92, Beta AFP, DPA, Reuters, Fena - 22/10/09)
